    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH2a1468-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:34:01.352+09:00">The sages admired wisdom</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-24T16:52:17.602+09:00">more than all else.  Shiji: 皇帝聰明，張守節注：聞見明辯。 孔穎達on　尚書堯典：聽遠為聰見微為明。</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-11-12T16:59:32.876+09:00">Of what intelligence values highly,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T17:59:22.576+09:00">there is nothing more valuable than to know men, 大戴禮記，衛將軍文子：故君子曰：智莫難於知人。 尚書，皋陶謨：知人則哲，能官人</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:10:12.315+09:00">being clear about personalities</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:11:51.924+09:00">is the general key to official personel]]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:38:47.254+09:00">and all those who know men are certainly wise.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:39:12.477+09:00">In this way all the abilities are put in their proper order</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-10-08T16:44:51.04+09:00">so that merit will prosper. 尚書，堯典：庶績咸熙。史記：眾功。</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:39:54.632+09:00">Therefore the sages composed the Book of Changes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:40:19.419+09:00">to establish the designations of the gentleman and the small man.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:41:46.165+09:00">They wrote the preface to the Odes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:42:00.178+09:00">in order to differentiate the elegance and orthodoxy of customs,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:42:55.729+09:00">and instituted ritual and music</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:43:23.333+09:00">inorder to examine the great and awesome virtues of the six arts.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T17:16:59.804+09:00">They set their faces southward</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T17:17:01.436+09:00">in order to use the abilities of the gentlemen.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T20:16:20.468+09:00">All these things were for the establishment of the various excellences, and the completion of the work of Heaven.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:46:21.928+09:00">When the work of Heaven has been completed,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:46:42.3+09:00">all will receive their proper classification and praise.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:47:47.935+09:00">Therefore Yao was commended for his ability to make capable and virtuous men distinguished.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:48:10.426+09:00">Shun made an achievement by using the sixteen illustrious men,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:48:42.625+09:00">Tang secured his reputation by using the worthy man of Youxin.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:49:31.153+09:00">Wen Wang was valued because of his using the old man of Weibin.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:49:47.135+09:00">We may conclude from this</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:50:04.538+09:00">that when the sages established their virtues,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:50:13.558+09:00">they exhausted their wisdom in finding men</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:50:36.076+09:00">and obtained comfort in appointing to office.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:51:07.417+09:00">Therefore if Zhongni had not examined his disciples</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:51:19.5+09:00">he could not have improved them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:51:49.604+09:00">So he divided his disciples into four groups,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:52:15.86+09:00">and differentiated all abilities into three categories.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:53:09.472+09:00">He also commended the doctrine of the mean, in order to distinguish the virtue of the sages.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.71" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:53:41.19+09:00">He esteemed virtue in order to urge the statement of approximations.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.79" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:57:35.155+09:00">He gave instructions concerning the six defects, in order to warn against the deficiencies of partial abilities.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.80" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:56:21.035+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.85" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:56:17.69+09:00">He thought of the ambitious and the conventional in order to bridge over the abilities of the conventional and the ambitious.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.90" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:58:06.452+09:00">He hated those who were ignorant but who were without sincerity,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.91" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:58:29.787+09:00">in order to show that the similitude is hard to preserve.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.96" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:59:06.868+09:00">He also said, "Examine what gives a man pleasure,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.97" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:59:39.931+09:00">and observe whence he comes,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.98" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T00:59:53.39+09:00">in order to know the actions of his ordinary behaviour.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.102" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:00:27.755+09:00">The investigation of men</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.103" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:00:53.783+09:00">in the greatest detail is like this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.106" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:01:48.358+09:00">Therefore I dare to follow the teachings of the sage</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.107" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:02:24.294+09:00">in composing this work,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.108" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:02:32.08+09:00">in order to mend my memory.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.109" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-21T01:16:09.248+09:00">And I wish that widely learned gentlemen should consider its significance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:31:13.716+09:00">[[tr. CH: Being proficient in writing and mathematics</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-10-08T16:21:23.122+09:00">is one of the six arts; 周禮，地官，保氏:掌諫王惡，而養國子以道，乃教之六藝，一曰五禮，二曰六樂，三曰五射，五曰六書，六曰九數。【賈公彥九章算術而言】</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:12:21.208+09:00">[[The gentleman is the petty man's teacher,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:12:32.456+09:00">and the petty man is the gentleman's aide.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:13:06.964+09:00">That teacher and aide bring each other to perfection,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:13:24.584+09:00">is something that has a long history.]]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:14:59.876+09:00">[[The nine continents have different customes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:15:15.697+09:00">and the five regions have different habits.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:34:02.892+09:00">Therefore the sage, as he establishes his teaching, does not replace what is local</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T22:17:04.532+09:00">and in organising the administration he does not try to change customs to the better.]]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-24T16:57:12.448+09:00">[[Commentary　tr CH: Heaven establishes the Images according to the three large lights (sun, moon, stars)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:30:36.449+09:00">man refines his capacities through intelligence.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:34:39.746+09:00">He may not change what is local</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:35:13.749+09:00">but he consistently puts the Odes and the Rituals first;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-09-23T23:35:43.562+09:00">he may not try to improve customs to the better,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1468_CHANT_001-1a.1-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2021-09-24T18:27:34.557+09:00">The Study of Human Abilities</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
